    "He pursued graduate work at New York University, teaching as an instructor in the department of art history at Emory University, Atlanta, GA in 1946 and the University of Louisville, Louisville, KY, the following year.": [],
    "He remained at Louisville until 1956 except for a year as Fulbright professor, University of Rome in 1951-1952.": [],
    "He published an early article, \"On Subject and Non-Subject in Renaissance Pictures\" in the <em>Art Bulletin</em> following his return.": [],
